    "c6fa4aab-6f2c-42e7-b1fa-d6690656899d": {
      "type": "custom-image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "fcd747ed-5c26-4c5c-ba37-91c9a6b18ed4": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><em><strong>Q: </strong></em><strong>Can you recall a moment where you took a risk or ventured into something new in your career, and how did it pay off?</strong></p><p><br/><strong>A: </strong>Taking risks is inherent in my line of work, especially when developing new products and styles. Starting my own company right after finishing my degree was a significant risk itself. Learning everything from scratch and making decisions independently has been an ongoing challenge. Currently, I'm in the process of launching a new collection of hand-painted wooden sculptures and exploring ceramics—a completely new avenue for me. Despite uncertainties, the experience has already been rewarding. The lessons learned and the personal satisfaction gained have been immense. Risks are necessary to grow and evolve!</p><p></p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
