    "776958e6-2b6f-43ce-939f-459bce151a1c": {
      "type": "custom-image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "1736fe90-b838-4ad5-9057-3f07ddd651f3": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><em><strong>Q: </strong></em><strong>Do you have a dream project or a vision for your professional future? How do you balance the business side of freelancing with your creative work?</strong></p><p><br/><strong>A:</strong> After nine years of running my brand, I've had the opportunity to work on diverse projects, which I'm incredibly grateful for. The dream for me is to continue being challenged, painting new spaces, and working on increasingly unique and different projects. Having the freedom to create what I truly want is essential. Sometimes, less challenging work allows me the freedom to invest time in personal creations and maintain that balance.</p><p><em><strong><br/>Q: </strong></em><strong>How have you stayed true to your passions and goals throughout your career journey?</strong></p><p><br/><strong>A:</strong> It's not always easy to prioritize and allocate time for my own creations while managing responsibilities. However, I remind myself constantly that I chose this path for a reason—to do what I love and have complete freedom in decision-making. Working independently requires self-motivation and a constant reaffirmation of the reasons behind pursuing a less conventional career. It's about embracing the freedom of choice and personal fulfillment.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
